{
  "stem": "10359.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "This is the saga of Ostrog.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Now, we came back.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I mean, nobody wanted to give us anything, even though they stole from the Jews.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Or maybe my aunt, or somebody else gave them some stuff to hold, to keep for after the war.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They said that they never took it, never got it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And a week later, they took me to the army.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To Ostrog?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, first of all, it was just about two, three days.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When we came in, was a very empty feeling, very strange feeling, because everything looked different.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was nobody there from our friends.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the people who were left there looked very suspiciously at us, not knowing what to expect.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were still afraid, because at that time they still had Ukrainian underground Bandera groups.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were afraid they could kill us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we didn't know why we came so soon, but we had no place to go.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So she stayed with Mrs.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH], the one that helped us for a couple of months to stay there, that her son was the policeman.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they took me into the army.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now before that, I forgot to mention the name of my friend, who kept going back and forth when she was in the hospital-- Wierzbicki, Csesek Wierzbicki.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He's now in Florida.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He came to visit her.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He came to help me to change some gold coins for paper money.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he was in touch with me all the time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That's the one who gave me the contact of his cousins in, in that Slavuta place, where the general was overseeing that place.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And after that, I lost contact with my other friend from Poland, Zygmunt Sinawski.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I just established contact with him about seven, eight years ago.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then, going back, we came to Ostrog.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "A week later, they took me to the army.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Took me to the army, they sent me to Siberia, to Chkalovsk-- which is 60 below zero-- for basic training.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So it's 60 below zero--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Russia, deep Russia, the uranium mountains.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I was there for basic training, for six weeks.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They had to give us a-- first like an officer school type of a thin.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then send me after-- yeah, I got some of hepatitis there, from the food or from whatever.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I stayed with their hospital for about two weeks.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "After that, they sent us to the front.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They sent us to Szczecin, which is in Poland, closer to the German border.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were fighting for a week, street fights.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And how I came alive, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "If you see it on television, how they do it, so you'll know how they do street fighting, and that's how we were fighting.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We took over Szczecin.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then we supervised the town, looking for some liquor and looking for some subversive or looking for whatever.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And after that, we went a few miles past Szczecin, staying there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Staying, and I tried to get a pass to go to Wroclaw, which is a town in Poland, and on the way there, to stop in Lodz where Dorothy was.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "When I came to Lodz, some of my friends from before the war, who escaped to Russia-- and they were active in the Zionist organization before the war, and they were active now as Aliyah Bet to help Jews to escape to Israel-- they told me take the uniform.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Get rid of the gun, get rid of everything.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Put some civilian clothes and we'll ship you to Austria or Czechoslovakia and Germany as a displaced person.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And they were looking for her, because she was a translator with all kinds of secret information.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And they were looking for me, because I actually escaped.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Now this was right after the war.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "The war ended in May 15, and this was probably, like, in June.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And so from there, we went to Czechoslovakia, then Austria, through the borders during the night as refugees or displaced people.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And we went to Germany, to the camp of Foehrenwald.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We stayed there for a month.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Then we went to Munich.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Then I worked in the Jewish committee, and I was chairman of the historical committee.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I was going to medical school.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And the reason I should have stayed there longer, because most of my friends finished medical school in Germany.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "When they came here, they were already more or less established.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "But being my brother was a doctor here, my sister was a doctor.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Her uncle was supposed to be rich.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "I figure that probably, when I come here, I will have no problem getting into school.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Unfortunately, I couldn't get into school so easily.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
